At http://closure-compiler.appspot.com/home
enter the below in the source texttarea



// ==ClosureCompiler==
// @compilation_level ADVANCED_OPTIMIZATIONS
// @output_file_name default.js
// ==/ClosureCompiler==

var o = {};
window['o'] = p;



Then hit the Compile button.

I expected to get



window.o={}




but actually got



window.o=p;



with nothing in either the warning or error tabs.

Two things:
1) "p" is unknown but the web-service runs with the equivalent of the command-line "--third_party", which assumes undefined variables are external values.
2) in advanced mode a global "o" and "window['o']" are not treated as equivalent:
http://code.google.com/closure/compiler/docs/limitations.html

Given #2, "var o" is unused and removed.

That said, assuming you didn't expect #2, I don't known why you would expect:
  window.o = {};
over:
  var o={};o=p;
or 
  var o={};window.o = p;
or 
  window.o = p;
